items.text: O come, let us sing unto the LORD: let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation.
items.plainText: O come, let us sing unto the LORD: let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation.

items.text: Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms.
items.plainText: Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms.

items.text: For the LORD is a great God, and a great King above all gods.
items.plainText: For the LORD is a great God, and a great King above all gods.

items.text: In his hand are the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills is his also.
items.plainText: In his hand are the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills is his also.

items.text: The sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land.
items.plainText: The sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land.

items.text: O come, let us worship and bow down: let us kneel before the LORD our maker.
items.plainText: O come, let us worship and bow down: let us kneel before the LORD our maker.

items.text: For he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. To day if ye will hear his voice,
items.plainText: For he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. To day if ye will hear his voice,

items.text: Harden not your heart, as in the provocation, and as in the day of temptation in the wilderness:
items.plainText: Harden not your heart, as in the provocation, and as in the day of temptation in the wilderness:

items.text: When your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my work.
items.plainText: When your fathers tempted me, proved me, and saw my work.

items.text: Forty years long was I grieved with this generation, and said, It is a people that do err in their heart, and they have not known my ways:
items.plainText: Forty years long was I grieved with this generation, and said, It is a people that do err in their heart, and they have not known my ways:

items.text: Unto whom I sware in my wrath that they should not enter into my rest.
items.plainText: Unto whom I sware in my wrath that they should not enter into my rest.
